    "Html": "<p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;font:normal normal normal 10px/normal helvetica;color:rgb(250, 128, 114);background-color:rgb(32, 32, 32)\"><span style=\"color:rgb(255, 245, 213)\">I updated from v6 to v7 and now I can't seem to load modules from the initialize() method of another module. You get stack overflow error.</span></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;font:normal normal normal 10px/normal helvetica;color:rgb(250, 128, 114);background-color:rgb(32, 32, 32)\"><span style=\"color:rgb(255, 245, 213)\"><br></span></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;font:normal normal normal 10px/normal helvetica;color:rgb(250, 128, 114);background-color:rgb(32, 32, 32)\"><span style=\"color:rgb(255, 245, 213)\">I changed the Dynamic Module Loading example to reproduce a similar problem.</span></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;font:normal normal normal 10px/normal helvetica;color:rgb(250, 128, 114);background-color:rgb(32, 32, 32)\"></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;font:normal normal normal 10px/normal helvetica;color:rgb(250, 128, 114);background-color:rgb(32, 32, 32)\"><span style=\"color:rgb(255, 245, 213)\">What I am trying to do is to have a common.module load ondemand and then retrieve other modules based on user profile. I was doing it in the initialize() method but that does not seem to work anymore. Is there an alternative way?</span></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;font:normal normal normal 10px/normal helvetica;color:rgb(250, 128, 114);background-color:rgb(32, 32, 32)\"><span style=\"color:rgb(255, 245, 213)\"><br></span></p><p style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;font:normal normal normal 10px/normal helvetica;color:rgb(250, 128, 114);background-c