    "Id": "204360",
    "ThreadId": "41927",
    "Html": "<p>Hi Damian Schenkelman,</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;In Silverlight and WPF LoginModule I just added these lines before loading the new module..&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.Height = 0;<br>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.Visibility = Visibility.Collapsed;<br>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;moduleManager.LoadModule(&quot;AdminModule&quot;);</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Now, I am able to see the admin module. Is there a better way of doing this?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Pooran</p>",
